This paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing the minimum cut on networks, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve tree packing and partitioning, which are common in algorithm design (cs.AL). The paper also mentions the network diameter, which is a metric commonly used in network analysis (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents an improved approximation algorithm, which is a topic of interest in theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
